  "name": "Genesis 23:1–25:18",
  "localizedName": "Genesis 23:1–25:18",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Abraham did several things to make sure that Isaac received the blessings of God’s covenant."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "When Isaac was young, Abraham sent Hagar and their son Ishmael away. When Isaac was older, Abraham also sent away the sons he had after Sarah died. He did this so that his children by his "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108265",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "concubines"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " wouldn’t cause problems for Isaac."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Abraham made sure that Isaac didn’t marry a Canaanite wife. He made sure that Isaac would continue living in Canaan after he married "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108266",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Rebekah"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". This was because God had promised to give the land of Canaan to Abraham’s family."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Abraham didn’t own the land yet. He even had problems with the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108267",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Philistines"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " taking over the wells he dug. The only land in Canaan that Abraham owned was the cave where Sarah was buried."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
